#: ../../source/user_guide/linear_solvers.rst:156
#: f3bb9704b8734cf4a07ef03bfa182c07
msgid "Batched right-hand sides"
msgstr "批量右端项"

#: ../../source/user_guide/linear_solvers.rst:158
#: bc2628fece1b48cba9d4935db21bf45a
msgid ""
"When ``b`` has shape ``[n_dof, n_batch]``, ``torch-sla`` automatically "
"amortizes the factorization across the batch — one factor pass, ``n_batch`` "
"back-substitutions — instead of running an iterative solver independently "
"per column. This is the workhorse of the :mod:`tensormesh.dataset` ML "
"workflow."
msgstr ""
"当 ``b`` 的形状为 ``[n_dof, n_batch]`` 时，\\ ``torch-sla`` 会自动将分解的开销摊销到整个 batch "
"上——一次分解、\\ ``n_batch`` 次回代——而不是对每一列独立运行一遍迭代求解器。这正是 :mod:`tensormesh.dataset`"
" 机器学习工作流的主力模式。"

#: ../../source/user_guide/linear_solvers.rst:169
#: d1edfdb506974e28b3662d7ad7cace12
msgid "See :doc:`batched_workflows` for the broader story on batching."
msgstr "关于批量化的更全面介绍，参见 :doc:`batched_workflows`\\ 。"

#: ../../source/user_guide/linear_solvers.rst:173
#: cc918ba898ab42048052fd60a7a3d067
msgid "Nonlinear systems: ``.nonlinear_solve()``"
msgstr "非线性系统：\\ ``.nonlinear_solve()``"

#: ../../source/user_guide/linear_solvers.rst:175
#: 1836beb8b39d4454a202053ea2764b4b
msgid ""
"For problems where the residual ``F(u, params) = 0`` is nonlinear in ``u`` —"
" hyperelasticity, plasticity, phase-field — use "
"``SparseMatrix.nonlinear_solve`` (inherited from "
"``torch_sla.SparseTensor``). The matrix is passed automatically into the "
"residual closure, the Jacobian is obtained through autograd, and the "
"backward pass uses the adjoint method."
msgstr ""
"对于残差 ``F(u, params) = 0`` 关于 ``u`` 非线性的问题——超弹性、塑性、相场——请使用 "
"``SparseMatrix.nonlinear_solve``\\ （继承自 ``torch_sla.SparseTensor``\\ "
"）。矩阵会被自动传入残差闭包，雅可比矩阵通过 autograd 获得，反向传播则使用伴随方法。"

#: ../../source/user_guide/linear_solvers.rst:200
#: 0701bde613374989a709ee8dd5ff09fe
msgid "Key keyword arguments:"
msgstr "关键关键字参数："

#: ../../source/user_guide/linear_solvers.rst:202
#: bb29dbd1a6fb4d4c847e45fcfe73017f
msgid ""
"``method``: ``\"newton\"`` (default, Newton-Raphson with Armijo line "
"search), ``\"picard\"`` (fixed-point), or ``\"anderson\"`` (Anderson "
"acceleration)."
msgstr ""
"``method``\\ ：\\ ``\"newton\"``\\ （默认，带 Armijo 线搜索的牛顿-拉夫森法）、\\ "
"``\"picard\"``\\ （不动点迭代）或 ``\"anderson\"``\\ （Anderson 加速）。"

#: ../../source/user_guide/linear_solvers.rst:205
#: be8ef5b5958a4441a7b76432098cec8a
msgid "``line_search`` (default ``True``) — toggle Armijo backtracking."
msgstr "``line_search``\\ （默认 ``True``\\ ）——开关 Armijo 回溯。"

#: ../../source/user_guide/linear_solvers.rst:206
#: 3f2fba25d55848f1bd88150321c46bab
msgid "``tol`` / ``atol`` / ``max_iter`` for the outer nonlinear loop."
msgstr "``tol`` / ``atol`` / ``max_iter`` 用于外层非线性循环。"

#: ../../source/user_guide/linear_solvers.rst:207
#: ff0cd6173f714ec0af1fe4b408fd7947
msgid ""
"``linear_solver`` / ``linear_method`` to pick the backend used for each "
"inner linear solve."
msgstr "``linear_solver`` / ``linear_method`` 用于选择每次内层线性求解所用的后端。"

#: ../../source/user_guide/linear_solvers.rst:210
#: e5a4e0a215574105a62c99e8037ece50
msgid ""
"The forward pass runs the chosen nonlinear iteration; the backward pass "
"solves a single adjoint system, so gradients of ``u`` w.r.t. any "
"``requires_grad`` parameter (including ``A.values``) cost roughly one extra "
"linear solve regardless of how many nonlinear iterations the forward took."
msgstr ""
"前向传播运行所选的非线性迭代；反向传播只求解单个伴随系统，因此无论前向走了多少次非线性迭代，\\ ``u`` 关于任何 "
"``requires_grad`` 参数（包括 ``A.values``\\ ）的梯度大约只额外花费一次线性求解。"

#: ../../source/user_guide/linear_solvers.rst:218
#: ed2d6d42250940cbb44087620996684f
msgid "Lower-level entry points (legacy)"
msgstr "更底层的入口点（遗留）"

#: ../../source/user_guide/linear_solvers.rst:222
#: 07fafcfc952f44d6aadca1902a90490d
msgid ""
":func:`tensormesh.sparse.spsolve` and "
":func:`tensormesh.sparse.nonlinear_solve` are TensorMesh-internal fallbacks "
"that pre-date the ``torch-sla`` integration. They are **scheduled for "
"removal**; the canonical solver path is the "
":class:`~tensormesh.sparse.SparseMatrix` (i.e. ``torch_sla.SparseTensor``) "
"methods above."
msgstr ""
":func:`tensormesh.sparse.spsolve` 和 "
":func:`tensormesh.sparse.nonlinear_solve` 是早于 ``torch-sla`` 集成的 TensorMesh "
"内部回退实现。它们\\ **已计划移除**\\ ；权威的求解器路径是上文介绍的 "
":class:`~tensormesh.sparse.SparseMatrix`\\ （即 ``torch_sla.SparseTensor``\\ "
"）方法。"

#: ../../source/user_guide/linear_solvers.rst:229
#: ac0676d66aea479ba707f0db145f26fd
msgid ""
":func:`tensormesh.sparse.spsolve` is a free function that operates on raw "
"COO arrays ``(edata, row, col, shape, b)`` instead of a "
":class:`~tensormesh.sparse.SparseMatrix` object. In practice this is rarely "
"useful — assembly produces a :class:`~tensormesh.sparse.SparseMatrix`, "
"condensation produces a :class:`~tensormesh.sparse.SparseMatrix`, and "
"``K.solve(b)`` covers every FEM workflow in this guide. "
"``tensormesh.sparse.spsolve`` will be retired once the remaining call sites "
"have moved over to ``SparseMatrix.solve`` / ``torch_sla.spsolve``."
msgstr ""
":func:`tensormesh.sparse.spsolve` 是一个自由函数，它直接操作原始 COO 数组 ``(edata, row, col,"
" shape, b)`` 而非 :class:`~tensormesh.sparse.SparseMatrix` "
"对象。实际上这很少用得上——装配会产生一个 :class:`~tensormesh.sparse.SparseMatrix`\\ ，凝聚也会产生一个 "
":class:`~tensormesh.sparse.SparseMatrix`\\ ，而 ``K.solve(b)`` "
"已涵盖本指南中的每一种有限元工作流。一旦剩余的调用点都迁移到 ``SparseMatrix.solve`` / "
"``torch_sla.spsolve``\\ ，\\ ``tensormesh.sparse.spsolve`` 即会退役。"

#: ../../source/user_guide/linear_solvers.rst:238
#: 506862a59d7c43dbac371c1827220cd9
msgid ""
":func:`tensormesh.sparse.nonlinear_solve` is the in-tree Newton-Raphson "
"helper. It requires the user to supply an explicit Jacobian closure and "
"lacks line search, Picard / Anderson modes, and the autograd-based Jacobian "
"assembly that ``torch_sla.SparseTensor.nonlinear_solve`` provides. Migrate "
"to ``A.nonlinear_solve(residual, u0, *params)``."
msgstr ""
":func:`tensormesh.sparse.nonlinear_solve` 是库内自带的牛顿-"
"拉夫森辅助函数。它要求用户提供一个显式的雅可比闭包，且缺少 ``torch_sla.SparseTensor.nonlinear_solve`` "
"所提供的线搜索、Picard / Anderson 模式以及基于 autograd 的雅可比装配。请迁移到 "
"``A.nonlinear_solve(residual, u0, *params)``\\ 。"

